<anchoringText id="Ancr2">Horizontal drilling has become an economic reality, and waterflood as a secondary recovery method is a proven cost-effective method for improving hydrocarbon recovery. However, this does not mean that horizontal wells with waterflooding guarantee the economic success of a project. Multiple realizations and development schemes must be evaluated through a series of economic filters such as net present value and economic limit analysis, sensitivity and scenario analysis on influential parameters such as the oil price, and operating cost. This project will be evaluated based on the project cost data shown in Table 2.</anchoringText>
